"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-04-05-olympics-qualifier-sports-minister-demands-better-performance-from-super-falcons\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  The Minister of Sports Development, John Owan Enoh, has urged the Super Falcons of Nigeria to do better when they face South Africa in the return leg of their 2024 Olympic Games final qualifying round tie.  The Super Falcons defeated the Bayana Bayana 1-0 in first leg of their 2024 Olympic Games final qualifying round tie in Abuja on Friday evening.  Captain Rasheedat Ajibade scored the only goal of the match to give Nigeria a slim victory over South Africa.  The Super Falcons created better chances in the early stages but failed to put any into the net.  Randy Waldrum's side will now face South Africa in the second leg in Pretoria next Tuesday.  Reacting, Enoh, in a tweet on his X account after the game, also congratulated the Super Falcons.  \\\"Congratulations, Super Falcons of Nigeria. Let us do even better in South Africa and pick the ticket for Paris Olympics,\\\" he tweeted.  \\\"To the supporters who came out to watch and cheer the Falcons, thank you.\\\"  Champions League: Gundogan picks team he wants Barcelona to play in final  Finidi wants fair officiating in Enyimba vs Lobi Stars  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Friendly: Cameroon coach gives reason for defeat to Super Falcons  Friendly: Babajide relishes Super Falcons' win over Cameroon  Friendly: Super Falcons floor Cameroon 3-1 in Yaounde  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"